a sad waste of talent expect no sparkle from stars or script in this remake of the witty comedy classic , which has been repeatedly filmed with varying degrees of success since 1931 . there is no chemistry between the male leads , and burnette is unspeakably bad in her cameo appearance . recommendation : see instead & quot ; his girl friday , & quot ; starring rosalind russel and cary grant ; it is easily the finest screen version of the famous stage play